<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>Very fast and very weak, the <b>Scorpion</b> packs a huge punch for its class and when used correctly is a supreme interceptor.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<p>A forerunner of this ship fought in the Boron Campaign and proved to be a pilot favorite. Like most other <a href="/index.php/Split" title="Split">Split</a> ships, this design focuses on high-speed engines and increased weapons power, at the cost of shield strength. Over the years the ship has been frequently updated and rearmed in order to remain as deadly as possible.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Variants">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Variants">Variants</span></h2>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Scorpion">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Scorpion">Scorpion</span></h3>
<p>Not featuring any fancy title, the basic version of the ship is the standard by which other variants are measured.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Scorpion Prototype">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Scorpion_Prototype">Scorpion Prototype</span></h3>
<p>Prototypes are pre-production test vehicles. They often feature higher speed and shields to help protect the valuable investment.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Scorpion Vanguard">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Scorpion_Vanguard">Scorpion Vanguard</span></h3>
<p>Vanguard variants of ships are slightly faster and have bigger weapons generators than their regular counterparts.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Scorpion Raider">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Scorpion_Raider">Scorpion Raider</span></h3>
<p>Raider variants are faster and usually have a higher shield generator power than their regular counterparts, but trade off cargo capacity and some have reduced shield capacity despite the more powerful generator.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Scorpion Sentinel">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Scorpion_Sentinel">Scorpion Sentinel</span></h3>
<p>Sentinel variants of ships tend to be slower, but with higher total shield capacity. Sometimes the shield class is also upgraded for instance from 25 MJ to 200 MJ.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Pirate Scorpion">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Pirate_Scorpion">Pirate Scorpion</span></h3>
<p>Pirate vessels are cobbled together from parts of captured ships. While often retaining the basic shape and configuration of the host vessel, pirate ships can be wildly different from the <i>official</i> variant, usually featuring unsanctioned weapons. Pirates sometimes decorate their ships with a distinctive flame motif.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Physical Characteristics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<p>Like all Split fighters, the Scorpion has a triangular, dagger-shaped hull and short, pointed wings.  It differs from its big brother, the <a href="/index.php/Mamba" title="Mamba">Mamba</a>, primarily in size.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Combat">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Combat"> Combat </span></h2>
<p>The Scorpion can be equipped with the powerful <a href="/index.php/HEPT" title="HEPT" class="mw-redirect">HEPT</a>, allowing it to demolish another <a href="/index.php/M4" title="M4">M4</a> with relative ease. However, its weak shielding is a big problem, which must be worked around either by flying it very evasively and carefully, or by using a pack that can demolish their prey before it gets a chance to fire back.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Scorpion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Equipment">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Equipment"> Equipment </span></h2>
<table bgcolor="white" align="center" style="border-style:dotted;border-width:2px;margin-top:5px;border-color:#aaaaaa">
